detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value:
This course has reserved seats for BMUS students. 

For non-BMUS students:
MUSC 100 is open to students in other departments and faculties, without pre-requisites.

MUSC 100 is a required course in the Major and Minor in Music.

If you're interested in the course, please register directly in the course, or if there are no seats remaining, join the waitlist.

Students with a declared Major or Minor in Music will have priority for registration from the waitlist.


Note that some lecture and discussion sections must be registered together:
MUSC 100 001 - students in this lecture section must register in either D01, D02, or D03

MUSC 100 002 - students in this lecture section must register in either D04 or D05

detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value: An introductory repertoire course for composers. This course focuses on compositional issues and approaches in art music of the past fifty years. Coursework includes listening, score study, readings, quizzes and in-class presentations. Restricted to undergraduate composition majors; other BMus students may register by permission of the instructor.

This class is one option that can satisfy the BMUS World Music requirement.

detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value: Large Instrumental Ensemble - UBC Concert WindsOpen only to 1st and 2nd year undergraduate students (see MUSC 350C for 3rd and 4th year registration; 550C for graduate registration).Open to non-music majors and secondary concentrators who are performers on woodwinds, brass, or percussion. Open to other students by audition, with credit, as stipulated by their faculties. May be repeated for credit. The ensemble rehearses MW 6-8:00 and makes four performances each year, with the majority of rehearsals and concerts taking place in the Chan Centre. While every effort is made to place students in appropriate ensembles based upon audition results, those taking this course as an elective are advised to have an alternate course ready in the unlikely case where an ensemble placement is not available. Entrance by audition each September. For more info: http://music.ubc.ca/student-ensembles

detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value: For 1st and 2nd year undergraduates (see MUSC 453A for 3rd and 4th year registration; 553A for graduate registration).OPEN TO NON-MUSIC STUDENTS: How do I register for ensembles? For most ensembles an audition is required to secure your place. During the audition you play or sing a prepared piece for the conductor. Auditions for ensembles take place at the beginning of each academic year. http://music.ubc.ca/student-ensemblesStudents who wish to be notified when the audition details are updated should ensure they are on the waitlist.
